rest_of_day_open: In the next week I see myself definitely having some highs and lows. If the weather is good and the people I enjoy are willing to hang out with me, I could see things being very good. If I feel isolated, and it's cold and rainy outside, it's likely I will feel quite badly.
critical_positive: We were both from the same general area of the United States, meaning we had some sort of basic connection right off the get go. We also had a connection based on a local university. She seemed genuinely interested in my answers and asked some follow-up questions which made for a pretty good conversation.
critical_negative: Between us, I felt there was something of a lack of connection based on our personalities and ourselves in general. We are both introverts, which can dampen the flow of the conversation.

rest_of_day_open: I see it going very well. I will do some household chores such as laundry and dishes. I will also homeschool my son every day except for the weekend and Friday. I will also do some gardening outside this weekend and plant more of my vegetables and flowers. Overall I think the rest of the week will be great.
critical_positive: I think what worked well is we were both college students so we could relate on that commonality. We also are both experiencing quarantine in the same state so we were able to relate quite well on that topic. We are both very friendly people that are introverts but I think we made it work well.

We are also in two different walks of life, him being a college student at age 19 and me being in my 30's.
